headline: Snow-ice warning for Carlow, Kilkenny, Laois, Longford, Wexford, Offaly, Westmeath, Cork, Tipperary and Waterford

headline: Weather Advisory for Connacht, Longford, Offaly, Westmeath, Cavan, Donegal, Clare, Cork, Kerry, Limerick and Tipperary
description:
Periods of heavy rainfall from Saturday to Tuesday may lead to some local flooding as river levels remain elevated.
The heaviest of the rain will be through Saturday afternoon, and again early Monday and early Tuesday, with rainfall accumulations from Saturday to Tuesday of 40 to 50mm in places, with some spot flooding.

Strong winds at times also, with gales on coasts.
areaDesc: Connacht, Longford, Offaly, Westmeath, Cavan, Donegal, Clare, Cork, Kerry, Limerick and Tipperary

description: Heavy rain today and overnight. 30 to 35 mm expected.
areaDesc: Dublin, Kildare, Laois, Longford, Louth, Wicklow, Offaly, Westmeath, Meath, Cavan and Monaghan

headline: Wind warning for Donegal, Leitrim and Sligo
description: Some severe winds expected during Saturday associated with Storm Jorge (Hor-hay).\nSouthwest quickly veering west and later northwest will reach mean speeds of 65 to 80km/h with gusts of 110 to 130km/h, possibly higher in very exposed areas with an elevated risk of coastal flooding.

headline: Rainfall warning for  Cork, Kerry and Waterford
description: Update on previous warning.\n30 to 50 mm of rain expected this evening, overnight and for a time on Friday with the risk of spot flooding.
